2. **MEDIUM `spec.unsupported-format-accepted`** (`bin/cli.js:60`): `const formatIndex = rest.indexOf('--format');` only looks at the FIRST `--format` occurrence. `node bin/cli.js version --format json --format yaml` currently exits 0 and prints `{"version":"0.1.0"}`, even though an explicitly supplied `--format yaml` should cause exit 1 per the Requirement "`--format yaml`, or any other value other than `json`, causes the process to exit with code 1". **Fix: validate every `--format` occurrence** (e.g. use `lastIndexOf` instead of `indexOf` so the LAST occurrence wins — standard CLI convention — or reject if any occurrence has a non-`json` value). Pick the smallest change; do not add a new dependency or new flag-parsing abstraction.

3. **LOW `consistency.inconsistent-error-shape`** (`bin/cli.js:67`, optional, only if trivial): `node bin/cli.js version --format` (flag with no value) prints exactly `Unsupported format: ` (trailing space, empty value), which reads a bit oddly next to the existing `--name requires a value` message style. This is a minor nitpick, not required — fix it only if it's a one-line, low-risk change; otherwise leave as-is.

